-- Chilean Stocks: Cap Posts Biggest Drop in Week, Ripley Falls
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2011-12-21T20:52:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/chilean-stocks-cap-heads-to-biggest-drop-in-week-ripley-falls.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa (IPSA)  index rose 0.5 percent to 4,199.56. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index retreated 0.4 percent to 2,257.43.  Cap SA (CAP)   dropped 0.7 percent to 18,990 pesos.
Chile’s largest iron ore miner and steel producer fell after
saying that the cost to develop its Cerro Negro Norte iron ore
project increased to $800 million.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   rose 0.3 percent to 12,377 pesos,
its fourth day of gains. Shareholders of Latin America’s largest
airline by market value approved today the company’s planned
takeover of  Brazil ’s Tam SA.  Ripley Corp SA (RIPLEY)   retreated 0.6 percent to 493.01
pesos. Chile’s third-largest department-store operator was
reiterated at “hold” at Santiago-based brokerage IM Trust SA
Corredores de Bolsa, according to an e-mailed note to clients.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
